[{"id":"7ea1da68fb458484762a3eb3cc57500f","from":"Unknown","from_email":"LVJET@aol.com","to":"JEEPROJECT@YAHOO.COM","to_list":[{"name":"JEEPROJECT@YAHOO.COM","email":"JEEPROJECT@YAHOO.COM"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"S76 offer","date":"2008-05-12T15:33:15.000Z","formatted_date":"May 12, 2008","formatted_time":"3:33 PM","body":"Jeffrey,\nSean has received an offer from a Brazilian  buyer, could be same as December \noffer.\n12.3M offer,,,Sean was told by broker they would go to  12.6M\nplease advise how to proceed?\nFor Mr. E  please.\n \nThis is an offer from  the Brazilians again.  Mr. Oliveria has suggested that \nhe would pay  $12.6.  He does not expect a response today an understands the \nowner may  not even see the offer until Monday.  I would suggest if we decided \nto  respond we draft a more formal Letter of Intent/Purchase Agreement with \nmuch  stronger language.   \nI have also been told  that we might see an offer next week from Wayne \nHuizenga next week.    \nSean J.  Lancaster \nBristol Associates  Inc. \n)+1-540-665-5135  direct \n(+1-202-682-4000 ext  1130 Main Office \n)+1-540-533-8183  Mobile \n4+1-540-301-0050  FAX \n_* slancaster@bristolassociates.com_ \n(mailto:%20slancaster@bristolassociates.com)  \n: _www.bristolassociates.com_ (http://www.bristolassociates.com/)   \nThis  message may contain confidential and/or legally privileged information. \n If  you are not the intended recipient of the message, please destroy it. \nAny  unauthorized dissemination, distribution or copying of the material in this \n message, and any attachments to the message, is strictly forbidden. (c) 2008 \nall  rights reserved. \n \n  \n____________________________________\n\nFrom:  ceo@planaer.com.br [mailto:ceo@planaer.com.br] \nSent: Friday, May 09, 2008 2:52  PM\nTo:  slancaster@bristolassociates.com\nSubject: OFFER TO PURCHASE YOUR 2007 SK76++  sn 760667\n \n \nDear   Sean,\n \n\n \nI have the  following offer to purchase for this helicopter sn  760667: \n \n\n \n1. The helicopter  shall be delivered in USA,  with the FAA  C of A export \ncertificate to Brazil or to Venezuela ( to  be advised) \n \n\n \n2. On the price shall  be included the SK76++ initial course, in the Flight \nSafety School. Courses for 2 Pilots + 2  mechanics ( at your costs)\n \n\n \n3. Our offer is U$  12.3Million.\n \n\n \n4. If you accept that  we can formalize and fax an OFFER TO PURCHASE with a \nU$ 150K in IATS-  Insured Aircraft Title Service, USA,  escrow refundable  \ndeposit,  to retire the helicopter from the market and schedulle the  acft. visit \nand the pre-purchase inspection.\n \n\n \nWe also need your  Aircraft Purchase Agreement draft to be analised and \napproved by our  attorneys\n \n\n \nThis offer is  valid until may 12, 2008 16:00hs local time.\n \n\n \nSincerely\n \n\n \nJose  A. Lins Oliveira     \nCEO\nPLANAER-Aviation Trade  Brazil\nPh 55-11-3476 9951  //  Cel.  55-11-9192 9887\nFax 55-11-5016 3860  \n_www.planaer.com.br_ (http://www.planaer.com.br/) \n \n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n**************Wondering what's for Dinner Tonight? Get new twists on family \nfavorites at AOL Food.      \n(http://food.aol.com/dinner-tonight?NCID=aolfod00030000000001)\n","body_html":"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN\">\n<HTML xmlns:o = \"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office\" xmlns:st1 = \n\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\"><HEAD>\n<META http-equiv=Content-Type content=\"text/html; charset=US-ASCII\">\n<META content=\"MSHTML 6.00.6000.16643\" name=GENERATOR></HEAD>\n<BODY id=role_body style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\" \nbottomMargin=7 leftMargin=7 topMargin=7 rightMargin=7><FONT id=role_document \nface=Arial color=#000000 size=2>\n<DIV><STRONG><FONT size=3>Jeffrey,</FONT></STRONG></DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG><FONT size=3>Sean has received an offer from&nbsp;a Brazilian \nbuyer, could be same as December offer.</FONT></STRONG></DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG><FONT size=3>12.3M offer,,,Sean was told by broker they would go to \n12.6M</FONT></STRONG></DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG><FONT size=3>please advise how to proceed?</FONT></STRONG></DIV>\n<DIV><FONT face=Arial color=navy><SPAN \nstyle=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\"><STRONG>For Mr. E \nplease.<o:p></o:p></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></DIV>\n<DIV>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Arial color=navy size=3><SPAN \nstyle=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></SPAN></FONT><FONT \nface=Arial color=navy size=3><SPAN \nstyle=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\">This is an offer from \nthe Brazilians again.&nbsp; Mr. Oliveria has suggested that he would pay \n$12.6.&nbsp; He does not expect a response today an understands the owner may \nnot even see the offer until Monday.&nbsp; I would suggest if we decided to \nrespond we draft a more formal Letter of Intent/Purchase Agreement with much \nstronger language.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Arial color=navy size=3><SPAN \nstyle=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></SPAN></FONT><FONT \nface=Arial color=navy size=3><SPAN \nstyle=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\">I have also been told \nthat we might see an offer next week from Wayne Huizenga next week.&nbsp; \n<o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Arial color=navy size=3><SPAN \nstyle=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\"><o:p>&nbsp;<FONT \nface=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&